.SH NAME
Gamepad.id \- Gamepad: id property
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]Secure context:\f[R] This feature is available only in secure
contexts (HTTPS).
.PP
The \f[B]\f[CB]Gamepad.id\f[B]\f[R] property of the \f[CR]Gamepad\f[R]
interface returns a string containing some information about the
controller.
.PP
The exact syntax is not strictly specified, but in Firefox it will
contain three pieces of information separated by dashes (\f[CR]\-\f[R]):
.IP \[bu] 2
Two 4\-digit hexadecimal strings containing the USB vendor and product
id of the controller
.IP \[bu] 2
The name of the controller as provided by the driver.
.PP
For example, a PS2 controller returned \f[B]810\-3\-USB Gamepad\f[R].
.PP
This information is intended to allow you to find a mapping for the
controls on the device as well as display useful feedback to the user.
.SH VALUE
A string primitive.
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP
.EX
window.addEventListener(\[dq]gamepadconnected\[dq], () \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  \f[B]const\f[R] gp = navigator.getGamepads()[0];
  gamepadInfo.textContent = \[ga]Gamepad connected at index ${gp.index}: ${gp.id}.\[ga];
});
.EE
